                      <note>
                            <date type="foundation" notBefore="1300" notAfter="1499"/>
                            <ab type="history">Gadām.</ab>
                            <ab type="tabot">
                                <measure quantity="6">6</measure> tābots, dedicated to 
                                <persName ref="PRS4327GabraMa" type="tabot">Gabra Masqal</persName>,                                
                                <persName ref="PRS3821entones" type="tabot">ʾƎnṭonǝs</persName>, 
                                <persName ref="PRS10581Zamika" type="tabot">Zamikāʾel</persName> and 
                                <persName ref="PRS6819Mary" type="tabot">Virgin Mary</persName>,
                                <persName ref="PRS4585Georgeo" type="tabot">St George of Lydda</persName>, 
                                <persName ref="PRS10775Trinity" type="tabot">Trinity</persName>.                                                               
                            </ab>
                            <ab type="description">28 priests and 16 deacons serve in the church (the stand for <date>December 2024</date>).
                                Only 70 manuscripts were inventarized on <date>in December 2024</date> by Hāgos Gabramāryām 
                                and ʾĀmanuʾel ʾĀbrha. According to the monks, the biggest part of the collection was destroyed by a 
                                lightning strike during a storm in the rainy season in 1996 EC (June to early September of 2004), at least 15 manuscripts
                                (including two manuscripts of <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1453GadlaG">the Vita of Gabra Masqal</ref>). The collection was 
                                endangered and damaged by fire at several occassions already before. 
                            </ab>
